{"questionId":"3627","questionHtml":"<p>State an equation for the formation of NO<sub>2</sub><sup>+</sup>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>HNO<sub>3</sub>&nbsp;+ 2H<sub>2</sub>SO<sub>4</sub> <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" \\rightleftharpoons \">\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇌</mo>\n</math></span> H<sub>3</sub>O<sup>+</sup> + NO<sub>2</sub><sup>+&nbsp;</sup>+ 2HSO<sub>4</sub><sup>–</sup><br><br></p>\n<p><em>Accept: HNO<sub>3</sub>&nbsp;+&nbsp;2H<sub>2</sub>SO<sub>4</sub>&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"&nbsp;\\rightleftharpoons \">\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇌</mo>\n</math></span>&nbsp;NO<sub>2</sub><sup>+&nbsp;</sup>+ HSO<sub>4</sub><sup>–&nbsp;</sup>+ H<sub>2</sub>O.</em></p>\n<p><em>Accept: HNO<sub>3</sub>&nbsp;+&nbsp;2H<sub>2</sub>SO<sub>4</sub>&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"&nbsp;\\rightleftharpoons \">\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇌</mo>\n</math></span>&nbsp; H<sub>2</sub>NO<sub>3</sub><sup>+</sup> + HSO<sub>4</sub><sup>–</sup>.</em></p>\n<p><em>Accept single arrow instead of&nbsp;equilibrium sign.</em></p>\n<p><em>Accept equivalent two step reactions in&nbsp;which sulfuric acid first behaves as&nbsp;strong acid and protonates nitric acid,&nbsp;before behaving as dehydrating agent&nbsp;removing water from it.</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"3627","referenceCode":"17N.2.hl.TZ0.8d","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"State an equation for the formation of NO2+.","paper":"2","level":"hl","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 20: Organic chemistry","20.1 Types of organic reactions","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 20: Organic chemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}